                               Info about the bands

DROWN IN EMBERS (written by Eike):
I have been playing in a variety of bands and band projects as a guitarist and bass player throughout my career. I joined Drown In Embers only 2 years ago with the other members knowing each other for decades already. 

We're doing Death Metal / Metalcore with a bit of Prog vibes here and there - unusual chord progressions or uneven meters might just happen during songwriting, but also trying to always keep it heavy at the same time. We're trying not to stick to the steretype kind of patterns of metal music and find our own style. Playing live is first priority. Our vocalist Nicki puts a lot of effort into the lyrics, that way that they actually serve as a framework for concept albums. 

We're the classic set of 5 guys: Vocals, 2x guitar, bassist, drummer. We released the EP "Remembrances of the Argonaut" and just recently two new singles, "Cyclus" and "Stockholm" which were also completely self-produced. 

https://drowninembers.com/
                              - - - - - - - - - -

PUTRID DEFACATION (written by Peter):
We play a style of death metal we call Toilet Slam, mainly as a reference to the toilet humour found in our song titles. The band started out as my solo project, but we currently have five members (and even includes another demoscener, Spiikki/Dekadence). We've been active since 2019 and have released a few EP's, some singles and a compilation album, with our debut album hopefully out before the end of this year. Previously we haven't played that many live gigs, maybe a few per year, but this year we've been more active on that front already playing a handful of gigs both in Finland and abroad (Estonia ja UK, with a festival gig in Germany coming up in late August).

http://putriddefecation.com
                              - - - - - - - - - -

